{
  "texts": [
    "We also take into consideration optional parameters.",
    "Incorrect Argument Type: Other than the error types mentioned above, we also observe that sometimes the model generates the correct argument's value, but in the wrong types.",
    "For example, when a parameter expects a [val1, val2, val3], the generated arguments is \"[val1, val2, val3]\", which is a string version of the list.",
    "When executing the function call, errors will occur due to incorrect data type.",
    "We identify trajectories containing the incorrect argument type error by comparing the parameter type in the available tools and the actual argument type."
  ]
}